HEADWORD: Poor-john
<hw>Poor"-john`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small European fish, similar to the cod, but of inferior
quality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Poor-john</qex> and apple pies are all our fare.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir J. Harrington.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poorliness</ent>⟦br⟧
